Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine orange-brown; pink in core. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Production date: 199 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0606)
